  <a href="/users/thisandthat" title="View user profile."><img src="/sites/all/themes/newsflash/images/bagicon.png" alt="thisandthat&#039;s picture" title="thisandthat&#039;s picture"  /></a></div>
</div><div class="author"></div>
    <p>They can lock you just on that alone - do you think you can hand over a computer and not associated passwords and not get in trouble for that? And if it was for something as non-trivial as control/survival of the system, how hard would you expect them to go on you? Would you be ready to be treated as, say, a terrorist with all that implies - and would it really be worth it, unless you're some activist willing to sacrifice yourself for your ideals (and what's the percentage of people willing to do it - you know, family, business, etc.)?</p>
<p>No problem is unsolvable if there's a solution somewhere - you just need to <em>squeeze </em>it out. Unless you're so rich, you're a systemic risk by yourself, that is - are you?...</p>

